# BuildTwin Frontend

Separate repo at `/home/mister-storm/development/buildtwin-frontend`. Backend is BuildTwin Kotlin at `:8080`.

## Data flow

UI components consume **domain models** from `src/features/domain/models/`, never `src/types/api/` DTOs directly. Mappers live in `src/features/domain/mappers/`.

## API integration

- Browser calls `/api/v1/*` (Next.js rewrite → `BUILDTWIN_API_URL`)
- Server Components fetch `BUILDTWIN_API_URL` directly

## OrthomosaicResolver

Pages depend on `OrthomosaicResolver` interface only. Default: `MockOrthomosaicResolver` with demo mappings. Viewer always validates via real APIs when backend is up.

## Demo mode

When backend offline, `DEMO_ENABLED` (default) serves Riverside Tower project. Orthomosaic preview: `/demo/orthomosaic-preview.jpg`.

## Logo

Run `npm run prepare:brand` after updating `~/Downloads/buildTwin.png`. Uses original brand colors with transparent background — do not invert colors.

## CSP (next.config.ts)

- Dev: `unsafe-inline` + `unsafe-eval` + `ws:` (React/Turbopack HMR)
- Prod: no `unsafe-eval`

## Forbidden

`any`, `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, `eval` in app code, direct DOM manipulation.
